+# mira-fault-detective — Disposition One-Pager
+
+**Date:** 2026-07-04 · **Status:** Proposed (decision for Mike)
+**Companion:** ADR-0025 (one diagnostic engine — Supervisor; everything else is a harness)
+
+## What it is
+
+A standalone MQTT-driven rule engine, 704 lines total (`mira-fault-detective/engine.py` 359 +
+`rules.py` 345, plus `tests/test_rules.py` / `test_http_api.py`). It subscribes to `$UNS_PREFIX/#`,
+evaluates priority-ordered rules over a `Snapshot`, **names a root cause** (`Diagnosis`), publishes
+it to `{prefix}/diagnostics/current_fault`, persists to its own SQLite table, and serves a
+token-gated read-only HTTP API on `:8077` (`/health`, `/current_fault`).
+
+## Evidence of current usage
+
+- **Deployment:** ONLY `docker-compose.fault-detective.yml`, whose 18-line header banner says
+  *"BENCH HARNESS — NOT a customer architecture"* and explicitly forbids promoting it to a
+  customer install. It appears in no customer compose (`docker-compose.yml`, `.saas.yml`,
+  `.staging*.yml`).
+- **Supervisor dependency (evidence-in, live):** `mira-bots/shared/engine.py:369`
+  (`_FAULT_DETECTIVE_URL`, default `http://mira-fault-detective:8077`) +
+  `_build_live_data_context()` / `_fetch_live_status()` (engine.py:3462–3486) pull
+  `/current_fault` as a flag-gated, never-raising `[LIVE EQUIPMENT STATUS]` enrichment block.
+  Covered by `tests/test_live_data_enrichment.py`.
+- **Marketing:** two comic-pipeline video scripts reference its HMI screenshots
+  (`marketing/comic-pipeline/scripts/phase5-video-13-ask-conveyor.yaml`,
+  `phase5-video-16-photo-to-plant.yaml` → `docs/promo-screenshots/2026-05-27_fault-detective-*`,
+  `2026-06-01_fault-detective-*`). Screenshots are append-only archive; no live dependency.
+- **Overlap:** SimLab (`simlab/scenarios.py`) already provides 6 replayable fault scenarios A–F
+  with ground-truth rubrics, run against the **real Supervisor** by `tests/simlab/runner.py`;
+  `simlab/diagnostic.py` is explicitly "an evidence-packet assembler — NOT an answer engine."
+
+## Options
+
+| Option | What it means | Verdict |
+|---|---|---|
+| **A. Productize behind the Supervisor** | Ship fault-detective as a cloud detector service; Supervisor consumes it as evidence | ❌ Not now. Its MQTT ingest + own persistence violate `.claude/rules/one-pipeline-ingest.md`; the customer-shipped detection path is the in-gateway Ignition rules (`plc/conv_simple_anomaly/rules_core.py`, A0–A12) per ADR-0021. Productizing means a rewrite through `mira-relay/ingest_contract.py`, not a promotion. |
+| **B. Fold into SimLab as detector + eval harness** | Keep `rules.py` as a pure detector library; port its conveyor fault map into `simlab/scenarios.py`-style replayable scenarios; keep the `:8077` evidence API for the bench; delete/deprecate its MQTT-publish of `Diagnosis` verdicts and its private SQLite persistence | ✅ **Recommended** — this is exactly ADR-0025's reclassification (detector + harness, never a customer-facing verdict). |
+| **C. Archive like mira-hud** | `archive/mira-fault-detective-2026-07` branch, remove from tree | ❌ Premature. The Supervisor's live-data enrichment path and the bench demo (which feeds the promo pipeline) still consume it. Archive only after Option B lands and the bench compose points at the SimLab-hosted detector. |
+
+## Recommendation
+
+**Option B.** Rationale: it resolves the only real problem — a second component that *names root
+causes* without citations or groundedness (ADR-0025 Context §2) — while preserving everything that
+is actually used: the rules as a detector, the `:8077` evidence feed into
+`_build_live_data_context`, and the bench demo behind the marketing screenshots. Concrete steps
+and the archive criterion are in ADR-0025 "Fold-in steps"; the one-line summary: **demote
+`Diagnosis` from verdict to evidence packet, move scenario replay into SimLab, keep the compose
+bench-only, archive the leftover shell afterwards.**
